        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 29 at 4:21PM MDT by NWS Denver CO</headline>
        <description>At 421 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 18
miles west of Forder, or 48 miles south of Limon, moving southeast
at 5 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Mainly rural areas of Southwestern Lincoln County.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
